														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1602622">
									

<p>Ah, okay.</p>
<p>Okay so 324's article says it was originally found in New Hampshire, which is like very far away from Mexico (Since you said &quot;village&quot; and everybody's speaking Spanish, I assume we're in Mexico), and the Foundation took all the samples away, the only explanation I can think of is that the original 324 bush came from Mexico, which, aside from being one HELL of a transplant journey, isn't supported anywhere in the original article. I'm not against the idea, it's just a bit of a stretch with such little supporting documentation.</p>
<p>Even so, like I said I really like this tale.</p>

							</div>

								
					
