														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1604704">
									

<p>I liked it. I don't see anything in spanish here very often, so i feel this as a fresh air.</p>
<p>By the way, in spanish, qhen you are talking about somebody's action in third person, is really normal to put &quot;el&quot; or &quot;la&quot; (translated in english would be &quot;The&quot; before the subject. for example:</p>
<p>Abuela maricela said it would pass/ The Abuela maricela said it would pass.</p>
<p>Actually you did it correctly, but it feels better for me in the second way.</p>

							</div>

								
					
